name: inverter production, for electric passenger car | inverter, for electric passenger car | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/1152/documentation

This dataset describes an inverter used in the power electronics of the drivetrain for an electric passenger car. It is based on direct information from Swiss manufacturer Brusa. The entries are given as a function of kg device. The specific inverter which was used for this dataset weights 9.5 kg and is suitable for a 100kW electric drivetrain.

The dataset starts with reception of  the electronic components used in the inverter, the efforts needed for the production of the components as well as the assembly of the converter.

The activity returns the fully assmebled inverter.
category: C:Manufacturing/27:Manufacture of electrical equipment/279:Manufacture of other electrical equipment/2790:Manufacture of other electrical equipment

processDocumentation.technologyDescription: This dataset is based on current, high-level standard.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: The data has been gathered between 2010 and 2011 and is expected, due to the high quality of the manufacturer, to be representative at least until 2015.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Data on materials and technology has been provided directly by the Swiss manufacturer Brusa.

exchanges.description: This dataset is based on direct information from the Swiss manufacturer Brusa.
